com.github.thorbenkuck.netcom2.network.shared.clients

Class ClientID

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.thorbenkuck.netcom2.network.shared.clients.ClientID
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    @Synchronized
public final class ClientID
extends Object
implements Serializable
    This Class is the Identification of any Client.

    Classes like the ClientList use this ID to identify any Client that has connected. Though this is mostly not needed, there are some needed Cases where this ID is compared and queried.

    For example, the establishment of a new Connection requires the Client to identify falsely create IDs to delete falsely create clients.

    1.0

      • fromString

        public static ClientID fromString(String s)
        Creates a new ClientID.

        This call uses a preset seed to determine the next ClientID. With this call, a specific ClientID can be created.

        This String has to be matched with the UUID implementation.

        Tho this appears handy, the use of this is not recommended. If you plan on creating the same ClientID for a Client every Time this Client Connects, don't.

        Parameters:
        s - the Seed that should be used
        Returns:
        a new ClientID instance
        See Also:
        UUID.fromString(String)

        public boolean isEmpty()
        Returns, whether or not this ClientID is empty or not.

        An Empty ClientID might be used, if an Client is not yet created correctly or if he has to be removed, but the remove is still in progress.

        Returns:
        true, if the ClientID is empty, else false.
